
= About the project =

== What are we working on? ==

First of~all, Luwrain is a~Linux-based specialized OS and a~place to~apply any new ideas  and experience.
Android, Tizen and FirefoxOS show that Linux turned~out as~a~wonderful base for~popular devices,
so current time to do this work is very fortunate. 
Once you get a~proper understanding of~LInux world you get a~clew what you should do if you'd like to~create new~cutting-edge technology.
We sure it~is a~chance as~we never had before to~solve rather  difficult problems in~area of~assistive technologies.

Meantime, one important thing should have additional clarification.
a~lot of~usual gadgets often  eventually considered   as~not~more valuable as~toys.
In case of assistive  technologies any doubts 
what exactly devices~are,   an~irreplaceable tool or an~item for~entertainment, are   completely improper.
They are always the~former as disabled persons are not~able to~do~without them.

We gathered our~project philosophy in~following ten brief statements:

# It is an OS completely designed for blind and visually impaired persons
# It must be convenient, fast and clearly understandable
# It~has~to support various languages and localizations
# It aims to be~sutable for~desktop computers as~well~as for mobile devices
# It is~based on~the~Linux kernel and other FOSS software
# No bias towards any particular  hardware type
# It~is a~non-profitable project
# Its auditory is all users who need it;
no~matter what experience  they got, 
what country are they from,
what profession are they occupied~in and so~on
# Everybody is~able to~participate in~its development,
but authors urge everybody to~respect accepted quality requirements for~all incoming patches
# We believe available experience in~GNU/Linux world is~enough at~least to~start this work and gives good base for~success

